Chinese President Xi Jinping on Wednesday sent a message of condolence to Greek President Katerina Sakellaropoulou over a train collision that has killed at least 36 people. In the message, Xi said he was shocked to hear that the accident has caused heavy casualties and extended condolences for the deceased and sincere sympathy to the bereaved families on behalf of the Chinese government and the Chinese people,Â wishing the injured a quick recovery.